measure end to end latency 
add latency measurement node (recommended)
Create a simple test node that:

Publishes a command to /cmd_vel with a timestamp
Subscribes to IMU data /imu/accel or /imu/gyro
Calculates delta between command sent → sensor response


Goal: 
Tuning Control Algorithms

Line following: If your camera processes at 28 Hz but motor commands lag by 200ms, the rover reacts to old vision data → poor tracking
PID tuning: Controller gains depend on loop timing. Variable latency breaks PID assumptions → unstable control


Debugging Performance Issues
Your system has:

Camera: 28 Hz
IMU: 20 Hz
LIDAR: 7 Hz
If latency is high, you can identify bottlenecks:

Is the RPi CPU overloaded?
Is the /cmd_vel callback blocking on I2C/serial communication?
Are there scheduling delays in ROS 2?


System Integration

Sensor-to-actuator loop: You need to know: "Camera sees line → process image → send steering command → motor moves" total time
If this loop is >100ms, you're reacting to stale data at any speed > 1 m/s